I doubt it.  You sent me some crappy ear buds which were not ordered by me.  I ordered the electric scooter.  If I do not have confirmation from you that the scooter was sent, I will have Citibank remove your charge from my account.  If the scooter does not exceed my expectations, I will return it, have the charge removed and aggressively report negatively about your products and service online.

To whom it may concern:
I have attached the last tracking update your company provided me on my recent purchase.  On December 7, 2018, it indicates that my item was delivered at 11:37 am, at my mailbox.  There was no delivery of any sort.  
Today, I waited for my mail carrier, who I know well, and inquired about the delivery that your tracking company stated was delivered 4 days ago.  She said she had no packaged delivery for me that day, and also confirmed that any packaged deliveries to my mailbox are not left at the mailbox, but in another secure location at my house.  None were done that day.  
Furthermore, I forwarded to her phone the updates, and delivery information, and tracking number from your tracking company, 17TRACK.  She took this information back to the postmaster and he investigated the tracking number and your company.  He called me and told me he had concern with the legitimacy of your company by the tracking number you provided.  A USPS tracking number is much longer and also contains certain letters and numbers specific to my mailbox location.  I never did receive a USPS tracking number.  He concluded this transaction and your company is probably fraudulent.  I have no other reason to believe the same.  
I paid $199.99 for on November 4, 2014, with my money transfeed to your company’s account November 6, 2018.  Unless you can provide me a legitimate USPS tracking number of the Stator motorized scooter that was paid for, I am telling you to refund my money in full.  A full refund is offered by your company if consumers are not satisfied.  I have also attached a screenshot of that when I purchased this item.
This is the start of my paper trail for my credit card company to begin reverses charges on this purchase.  This is what they have advised me to do before they begin legal proceedings.  
I would appreciate your cooperation in dealing with this matter.  Thank you for your time.
Sincerely, Marcella Murdoch

Hi

Are you just replying to me to make it look like there was some sort of mistake? You sent me all the tracking information that was online and attached to the wireless earphone I got instead of my scooter. You have had well over a month to reply to even my first email regarding how long it would take to deliver my scooter and you didnt so I am now wondering if you are just trying to look helpful because there has been an issue raised with my bank about my payment to you.

There is no excuse for what has happened here and it has been made very clear by you website change and the fact that my scooter was no longer advertised on your website even just a few days after I bought it that this seems to be some sort of scam. I work hard for my money and wanted to treat myself to nice electric scooter which was to be used for taking my little nephew out and commute to work.

I will not let myself be scammed by your company and I trust that with all the information I have sent to my bank regarding this matter that you will not be getting any more money from me. This just goes to show that some people will not stand for false advertising and scamming and I think you should be ashamed of yourselves.

Kind Regards
Alana Macrae
